body.description: The white colored Shadow Wings 2 120mm PWM offers whisper-quiet operation and reliable cooling at low revolutions per minutLow-noise operation of up to 15. 9dB(A) even at its maximum speed of 1, 100 rpmAirflow-optimized fan blades, resulting in a whisper-quiet operation yet solid coolingAnti-vibration mounting system that prevents transmission of vibrations to your PC caseRubberized fan frame minimizes vibrationsHigh-grade rifle-bearing technology that contributes to an operating lifetime of 80, 000 hoursSecure and easy installation of the fan with push-pinsPWM controlled fan speed through the motherboardProduct conception, design and quality control in Germany3-year manufacturer’s Shadow Wings 2 fans are the perfect choice for all who appreciate maximum silence for their PC case.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Low-noise operation Whisper-Quiet Operation The Shadow Wings 2 120mm PWM White fan blades have been optimized to ensure maximum airflow, resulting in a whisper-quiet operation yet solid cooling. They operate at only 15.9 dB(A) even at its maximum speed of 1,100 rpm. The perfect choice for all who appreciate maximum silence for their PC case. Anti-Vibration Concept Removable anti-vibration mountings on all four edges of the fan reduce vibrations transmitted to the PC case. In addition, the fan is equipped with a rubberized frame that reinforces the anti-vibration concept and ensures vibrations are reduced to an absolute minimum. Rifle Bearing Technology The Shadow Wings 2 120mm PWM White is the hallmark of outstanding reliability. This is achieved by its high-quality rifle bearing technology, which assures a very long lifespan of up to 80,000 hours.

User-friendly Installation Push-Pin Mounting With the Shadow Wings 2 anti-vibration mounting system the fan is simple to install. The push-pins ensure a very fast and secure installation without needing screws. Variable Fan Speed Function Pulse Width Modulation (PWM) allows compatible 4-pin controllers to vary the speed intelligently and thus minimize the noise level of the fan. With PWM your system can ramp up the cooling when it’s needed, or operate at maximum quietness when it’s not.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cool and quiet German fans
reviews.reviewText: They are not cheap, which is why I could not justify buying them for original 20 bucks price.But they are so quiet and awesome looking that eventually I got em on sale.They look very simple (no rgb) but at the same time so very stylish and cool looking inside a case.I might be subjective, I am a fan of everything BeQuiet.I highly recommend these to anyone who wants qualityfans without rgb lights.

reviews.reviewText: Perfect finishing touch for my daughter's rig.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Boy these things are silent. CFM of airflow is right where you would want it to be, and their bladed in a way that favors radiators on water-cooled computers. Also, a lot of thought went into them performing well as case fans as well. A little measuring shows them quite energy efficient (more so than the Corsair Mag-Lev fans I run, and quieter).Be Quiet, if don't know is an excellent company that makes quality, high-end products at reasonable prices. It shows here.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2021
reviews.reviewText: They're a bit expensive, but if you're sensitive to noise or want the most silent PC possible, these fans are worth it. I have four (3x 140mm and 1x 120mm) in my NZXT H500 and I have *never* heard them since installing them a few months ago. PWM function works great and I think these fans look super clean in a mostly-white build. The installation was AWESOME too because there are no screws involved, just little plastic pieces that are really easy to take on and off.I actually became a bit of a be quiet! stan because of these fans; since getting them, I've bought a new Straight Power 11 PSU and a Shadow Rock 3 (White edition) CPU cooler. Both of those products have also been completely silent and are worth the cost.TLDR; pricey but dead silent. 9/10

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I purchased a white be quiet! pure base 500 case for my latest build. The case comes with (2) 140mm be quiet! pure wings 2 black fans. While these are truly excellent and quiet fans and an incredible value in the case at the price point, I wanted an all white build. I grabbed one be quiet! Shadow Wings 2 white fan when Amazon finally had one in stock.I love it! It runs quieter at a higher RPM than the pure wings fan and looks great in my build. When the white versions become available again, I am going to pick up another one or two to replace the black fan that is still in my case. That said, my case is virtually silent as is, but I expect even with a 3rd Shadow Wings fan, it will be even silenter (if that is even a word).In all - I love be quiet! products and love this Shadow Wings 2 140mm white case fan.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Quiet and best of all keep my pc cool I'll never switch back to another fan 10/10 would recommend to anyone looking to buy these.
Have used “Be Quiet” older gen fans in the past. They were always good, but these newer gen ones are their best yet that I’ve tried. Also love the colour. Too bad the wires were not also in white.

Auch wenn se nich ein paar Euro günstiger sein dürften.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on October 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Looks cool and quiet in my full white setup.

reviews.reviewTitle: Sehr leiser Gehäuselüfter mit einer hochwertigen Qualität
reviews.reviewText: Der Lüfter ist als Rear-Lüfter in einen Linux Rechner verbaut und macht dort einen tollen Job. Er ist absolut geräuschlos und schaufelt dabei jede Menge heißer Luft aus den Gehäuse.Die Qualität ist be quiet mäßig auf einen sehr hohen Niveau. Die Montage ist sehr einfach und erstklassig.Verbaue schon Jahrelang bq und habe es bis heute nicht bereut.

Bisher bin ich super zufrieden mit den Lüftern. Sie waren einfach zu verbauen, kühlen meinen Tower und sind dazu noch absolut leise.Ich hatte vorher mitgelieferte Gehäuselüfter verbaut und das ist gar kein Vergleich zu den jetzigen von beQuiet. Manchmal merke ich gar nicht, dass der PC überhaupt eingeschaltet ist.Auch beim Spielen von PC-Games ist das Geräusch der Lüfter nicht nervig. Sie drehen natürlich mehr auf, aber das sollen sie auch und ist total im Rahmen! Ich bin zufrieden!
